             <item>
              <widget class="QLabel" name="labelTermsBody">
               <property name="text">
                <string>Last updated: March 2026

Welcome to Aethera. By accessing or using our application, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions.

1. Acceptance of Terms
By creating an account or using Aethera, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these terms.

2. Use of the Application
Aethera is an educational platform designed for learning and examination purposes. You agree to use the application only for lawful purposes and in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations.

3. User Accounts
You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials. You agree to notify Aethera immediately of any unauthorized use of your account.

4. Intellectual Property
All content, features, and functionality of Aethera, including but not limited to text, graphics, logos, and software, are the property of Aethera and are protected by intellectual property laws.

5. User Content
Any content you submit through Aethera, including profile information and exam responses, remains your property. However, you grant Aethera a non-exclusive license to use this content for the purpose of providing and improving our services.

6. Limitation of Liability
Aethera is provided &quot;as is&quot; without warranties of any kind. Aethera shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the application.

7. Termination
Aethera reserves the right to suspend or terminate your account at any time for violation of these terms. You may also delete your account at any time through the Settings page.

8. Changes to Terms
Aethera reserves the right to modify these terms at any time. Continued use of the application after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.

9. Contact
If you have questions about these Terms and Conditions, please contact the Aethera support team.</string>
