             <item>
              <widget class="QLabel" name="labelPrivacyBody">
               <property name="text">
                <string>Last updated: March 2026

Aethera is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information.

1. Information We Collect
Aethera collects the following information when you create an account:
  • Username and password
  • Grade level
  • Profile information (bio and profile picture)
  • Exam results and performance data

2. How We Use Your Information
Your information is used to:
  • Provide and maintain your Aethera account
  • Track your learning progress and exam performance
  • Improve our educational content and services
  • Personalize your Aethera experience

3. Data Storage
All data is stored locally on your device. Aethera does not transmit your personal information to external servers.

4. Data Security
Aethera implements appropriate security measures to protect your personal information. However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

5. Your Rights
You have the right to:
  • Access your personal information
  • Update or correct your profile data
  • Delete your Aethera account and all associated data

6. Children's Privacy
Aethera is designed for educational purposes and may be used by minors. We do not knowingly collect personal information beyond what is necessary for the educational experience.

7. Changes to This Policy
Aethera may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes through the application.

8. Contact
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact the Aethera support team.</string>
